1. Aeneadum genetrix: Lucr. strikes a national note: Venus, mother of Aeneas, is also mother of his descendants, the Roman people.

Just as the Aeneid is often referred to by Latin poets as Arma uirumque, and Book i of Propertius as Cynthia, so the poem of Lucr. is referred to by Ovid T rz‘st. ii 261 sumpserit, Aeneadum genetrix ubi prima (if she takes up the work, where Aeneadum genetrix comes first).

genetrix is the true spelling in spite of genitor: so meritus but meretrix.
